article_title: Free safety Rahim Moore to visit with Houston Texans – The Denver Post
article_text:
Free safety Rahim Moore is scheduled to visit with the Houston Texans, an NFL source confirmed.

The Broncos are monitoring Moore’s negotiations in free agency, but it appears less and less likely that they will have the budget room to make a competitive offer.

Moore, a second-round draft pick by the Broncos in 2011, was a three-season starter who had four interceptions and six unassisted tackles in 2014-15.

Mike Klis: mklis@denverpost.com or twitter.com/mikeklis
